🚨 Alerting (Prometheus + Alertmanager)
⚙️ Implementation

Alerting is handled by Alertmanager, which is part of the kube-prometheus-stack.

Key Components
Prometheus → evaluates alert rules
Alertmanager → sends notifications
Grafana → optional visualization of alerts
🔔 Alert Rules

Custom alert rules were defined for the application:

🔹 High CPU Usage
expr: sum(rate(container_cpu_usage_seconds_total{namespace="chiara-app"}[5m])) > 0.8
for: 2m

Purpose:

Detect high CPU consumption
Prevent performance degradation
🔹 Pod Restarts
expr: increase(kube_pod_container_status_restarts_total{namespace="chiara-app"}[5m]) > 0

Purpose:

Detect crashes or unstable deployments
🔹 Pod Down
expr: count(kube_pod_status_phase{namespace="chiara-app", phase="Running"}) < 1

Purpose:

Detect service downtime
📣 Notification Channels

Alertmanager can be configured to send alerts to:

Email
Slack
Webhooks
🎯 Outcome
✔ Automatic detection of failures  
✔ Immediate notification when issues occur  
✔ Reduced reliance on manual monitoring  
📜 Logging (Loki + Promtail)
⚙️ Implementation

Logging is implemented using:

Loki – log storage
Promtail – log collector
Grafana – log visualization
🔄 Log Flow
Pods → stdout/stderr
        ↓
Promtail
        ↓
Loki
        ↓
Grafana (Explore / Dashboards)
📥 Promtail

Promtail runs as a DaemonSet and:

Collects logs from all nodes
Attaches Kubernetes metadata (namespace, pod, container)
Sends logs to Loki
🗄️ Loki

Loki stores logs in a structured way using labels:

namespace
pod
container

Unlike traditional logging systems, Loki does not index full log content, making it lightweight and efficient.

🔍 Grafana Integration

Loki is added as a data source in Grafana.

Log queries example:
{namespace="chiara-app"}

Filter by pod:

{namespace="chiara-app", pod=~"chiara-app-.*"}
🎯 Outcome
✔ Centralized log collection  
✔ Real-time log visibility  
✔ Ability to debug issues quickly  
✔ Correlation between metrics and logs  
🧠 Combined Observability

With monitoring, alerting, and logging:

Metrics → What is happening  
Alerts → When something is wrong  
Logs → Why it went wrong
⚠️ Challenges & Fixes
Issue	Cause	Resolution
Alerts not firing	Incorrect PromQL	Fixed expressions and thresholds
No notifications	Alertmanager not configured	Added receivers (email/slack)
Logs not visible	Promtail misconfiguration	Verified log paths and labels
Missing labels	Kubernetes metadata not attached	Fixed Promtail config
